@startuml referral_fraud_engine_flow_v2
title Referral Journey with Fraud Engine (Signup Never Blocked - Payout is the Gate)

actor "Referrer\n(User A)" as ReferrerUser
actor "Referee\n(User B)" as RefereeUser
participant "Host System\n(Bank App/)" as Host
participant "Vigilant Engine\nAPI" as Engine
database "Graph Store\n(Neo4j)" as Graph
participant "Scoring\nEngine" as Scorer
participant "Case Queue /\nDashboard" as Dashboard

== Step 1: Code Request ==
ReferrerUser -> Host: Request referral code
Host -> Engine: POST /v1/codes/generate\n{userId, deviceId, ipAddress}
Engine -> Graph: check identity fingerprint\n(existing nodes with same device/IP?)
Graph --> Engine: fingerprint match results
Engine -> Scorer: pre-check identity risk
Scorer --> Engine: risk score
Engine -> Graph: create/update referrer node\n(regardless of risk - just tagged if risky)
Engine --> Host: {status: ISSUED, referralCode, riskFlag}
Host --> ReferrerUser: Referral code returned

note right of Engine
  Code issuance is never denied.
  A risky identity is tagged on the
  node so it carries forward into
  later scoring, not blocked here.
end note

== Step 2: Sharing (no system event) ==
ReferrerUser -> RefereeUser: Shares referral code\n(out of band - WhatsApp/SMS/etc)

== Step 3: Redemption - always allowed ==
RefereeUser -> Host: Signs up using referral code
Host -> Engine: POST /v1/events/redemption\n{referralCode, newUserId, deviceId, ipAddress}
Engine -> Graph: create REFERRED edge\n+ SHARES_DEVICE / SHARES_IP edges if matched
Engine -> Scorer: run cheap real-time checks\n(velocity, device/IP collision)
Scorer --> Engine: redemption-time risk score
Engine -> Dashboard: soft-flag case if risk elevated\n(async, informational only)
Engine --> Host: {action: ACCEPT}
Host --> RefereeUser: Signup proceeds normally\n(always)

note right of Host
  No path here ever rejects
  or delays the signup itself.
end note

== Step 4: Conversion (qualifying action) ==
RefereeUser -> Host: First deposit / transaction / N-day retention met
Host -> Engine: POST /v1/events/conversion\n{referralCode, refereeUserId, conversionType}
Engine -> Graph: pull referrer subgraph\n(depth N, multi edge-type)
Graph --> Engine: subgraph data
Engine -> Scorer: full scoring pass\n(graph structure + identity overlap + behavioral + prior soft-flags)
Scorer --> Engine: score + reasonCodes

Host -> Engine: POST /v1/decisions/payout-check\n{referralCode, refereeUserId}

alt score < low threshold
    Engine --> Host: {action: APPROVE, score}
    Host -> Host: Release KES 350 bonus to referrer
    Host --> ReferrerUser: Bonus credited
else score in medium band
    Engine --> Host: {action: HOLD, score, reasonCodes}
    Host --> ReferrerUser: Bonus marked "pending review"
    Engine -> Dashboard: create case for manual review
    ...analyst reviews asynchronously...
    Dashboard -> Engine: analyst decision (approve/reject)
    Engine -> Host: async webhook: final decision
    Host -> Host: release or cancel bonus accordingly
    Host --> ReferrerUser: notified of final outcome
else score > high threshold
    Engine --> Host: {action: REJECT, score, reasonCodes}
    Host -> Host: cancel bonus (never released)
    Host --> ReferrerUser: bonus not awarded
    Engine -> Dashboard: log auto-rejected case for audit
end

== Ongoing: Batch Re-analysis ==
Graph -> Scorer: nightly job pulls full graph
Scorer -> Scorer: re-scan for ring patterns\n(cycles, multi-edge overlap, cohort outliers)
Scorer -> Dashboard: surface newly-detected clusters\n(may retroactively flag already-paid bonuses for clawback review)
Dashboard -> Dashboard: feed analyst decisions back\nas labeled data for rule/threshold tuning

@enduml